<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
Referring to a printing process, in particular <a title="Lithography" href="Lithography">lithography</a>, in which the image area of the plate carrying the image to be printed is the same height (or on the same plane) as the non-image areas. Planographic printing processes use the principle of chemical repulsion between oil-based inks and water to keep image areas and non-image areas separate. (See <a title="Lithography" href="Lithography">Lithography</a>.) 
</p>
